1 A BILL for an Act to amend and reenact section 54-59-11 of the North Dakota Century Code,
2 relating to information technology plans; and to repeal section 54-59-11.1 of the North Dakota
3 Century Code, relating to information technology project planning.
4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
5 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Section 54-59-11 of the North Dakota Century Code is
6 amended and reenacted as follows:
7 54-59-11. Information technology plans.
8 Each executive branch state agency or institution, excluding the institutions under the
9 control of the board of higher education, unless the chief information officer grants an
10 exemption, shall participate in the information technology planning process based on guidelines
11 developed by the department. The plan must be submitted to the department by August
12 fifteenth of each even-numbered year unless the chief information officer grants an extension.
13 The department shall review each entity's plan for compliance with statewide information
14 technology policies and standards and may require an entity to change its plan to comply with
15 statewide policies or standards or to resolve conflicting directions among plans. Agencies of the
16 judicial and legislative branches shall file their information technology plans with the department
17 by August fifteenth of each even-numbered year. Based on the plans, the department shall
18 prepare a statewide information technology plan and distribute copies of that plan to members
19 of the legislative assembly as requested by the legislative council. The statewide information
20 technology plan must be developed with emphasis on long-termagency strategic goals,
21 business objectives, and accomplishmentsalignment to statewide information technology
22 initiatives.
